HEADWORD: Homager
<hw>Hom"a*ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Homage</er>: cf. F. <ets>hommager</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who does
homage, or holds land of another by homage; a vassal.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

